One of the annoying things about AI image generation software is that there is not really any standardization, not even in prompt format, from one build to the next. This one can't use this one's lora files. This one doesn't understand this big subset of prompts. This one requires line breaks instead of commas in the prompt area. This one requires commas instead of line breaks. Everything you see that's freely downloadable is being done by groups of hobbyists who are constantly changing everything, big and little, and putting out new versions. If you're using Automatic1111 you need their checklist. The checklist for Shark or ComfyUI or Vladmandic won't work, and there may be differences in required prompt syntax also. It reminds me of the early Wild West days of Linux, actually, when every other hobbyist cobbled together his own distro.
